Over the years, it has undergone major transformations to enhance its offerings, aiming to be the leading amusement park in the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia.'], 'Key Features': ["Roller Coaster: Experience high-speed thrills with loops and sharp turns on the park's signature roller coaster.", "Ice Skating Rink: Enjoy ice skating in a unique indoor setting, providing a cool escape from the city's warmth.", 'Amazon Forest: Embark on a boat ride through a jungle-themed area featuring life-size animal figures, waterfalls, and immersive light and sound effects.', 'Themed Areas: Explore various sections like the European Village and Far East Village, each offering distinct architectural styles and dining experiences.', 'Entertainment Building: Features an arcade, bowling alley, billiards, karaoke, and party rooms suitable for private events and gatherings.'], 'Working Hours': ['Operating Hours: The park operates daily with varying hours:', 'Saturday to Wednesday: 5:00 PM – 1:00 AM\u200b.', 'Thursday and Friday: 5:00 PM – 1:30 AM\u200b.']}

name: Makkah Gate
description: {'Information': ['Makkah Gate, also known as Bab Makkah, is a historic gateway located at the eastern entrance to Jeddah, Saudi Arabia. Constructed in the 16th century during the Ottoman era, it served as the primary entrance for pilgrims traveling from Jeddah to Makkah for Hajj.', 'The gate is characterized by its three arches and flanking towers, reflecting traditional Islamic military architecture.', "Makkah Gate holds significant historical value as it marks the boundary of the Haram area, a sacred zone surrounding the city of Makkah where non-Muslims are prohibited. It has witnessed the passage of countless pilgrims over centuries, underscoring Jeddah's role as the main port for Hajj travelers."], 'Key Features': ['Architectural Design: The gate features three prominent arches with decorative patterns and is flanked by two towers, embodying Ottoman architectural influences.', 'Location: Situated in the Al-Balad district, a UNESCO World Heritage site, the gate is surrounded by traditional markets and historic buildings.'], 'Working Hours': ['Makkah Gate is an outdoor historical monument and is accessible at any time. However, visiting during daylight hours is recommended to fully appreciate its architectural details and the lively atmosphere of the surrounding district.']}
short_description: Makkah Gate is a historic 16th-century archway in Jeddah, marking the entrance to Makkah and serving as a testament to the city's rich history as a gateway for pilgrims.

name: Jeddah Waterfront Park
description: {'Information': ['Jeddah Waterfront Park, situated along the Red Sea coast, is a vibrant destination offering a blend of recreational and cultural experiences.', 'The park features lush green spaces, walking and cycling paths, and dedicated play areas for children. Visitors can enjoy various sculptures and art installations that enhance the aesthetic appeal of the area.', 'The park is also equipped with amenities such as seating areas, restaurants, and restrooms, ensuring a comfortable visit for all.', "Inaugurated in 2017, the Jeddah Waterfront Park was developed as part of a broader initiative to revitalize the city's coastal areas, aiming to provide both locals and tourists with a modern recreational space that celebrates Jeddah's rich cultural heritage."], 'Key Features': ['Recreational Facilities: The park offers designated areas for picnics, jogging, and cycling, promoting an active lifestyle among visitors.', 'Art Installations: Scattered throughout the park are numerous sculptures and artworks that contribute to its unique ambiance.', "Children's Play Areas: Safe and engaging playgrounds are available, equipped with modern play structures suitable for various age groups.", 'Dining Options: A variety of restaurants and cafes line the waterfront, offering diverse culinary delights with scenic sea views.'], 'Working Hours': ['Jeddah Waterfront Park is open 24 hours a day, allowing visitors to enjoy both day and night views of the Red Sea.']}
short_description: Jeddah Waterfront Park offers green spaces, art, play areas, and dining with stunning sea views.

name: Al Taybat International City Museum of Science and Information
description: {'Information': ['The Al Tayebat International City Museum of Science and Information, located in Jeddah, Saudi Arabia, is a comprehensive museum complex encompassing 12 buildings with over 300 rooms. Established in 1987, it offers an extensive collection of artifacts and exhibits that showcase the rich history, culture, and heritage of the region.', "Originally constructed as the residence of Sheikh Abdul Rauf Khalil, the complex was transformed into a museum to preserve and display a vast array of historical and cultural items. It serves as a testament to the region's evolution, highlighting Islamic civilization, Saudi heritage, and various international influences."], 'Key Features': ['Architectural Design: The museum complex is designed in the traditional Hijazi architectural style, featuring intricate woodwork, carved doors, and a central courtyard with fountains and palm trees, reflecting the historical aesthetics of the region.', "Diverse Exhibits: The museum houses over 60,000 artifacts, including Islamic manuscripts, ancient coins, traditional costumes, furniture, pottery, and more, offering a comprehensive insight into the area's cultural and historical landscape.", "Specialized Sections: The museum is divided into 18 wings, such as the General Culture Section, Islamic Civilization Section, Saudi Heritage Section, and General Heritage Section, each providing in-depth knowledge about different aspects of the region's history and culture."], 'Working Hours': ['Saturday to Thursday: 8:00 AM – 12:00 PM and 5:00 PM – 9:00 PM.', 'Friday: Closed.']}
short_description: Al Tayebat Museum in Jeddah showcases Saudi heritage and Islamic culture with over 60,000 artifacts.

Its strategic location and distinctive architecture make it a notable landmark in Jeddah, reflecting the city's rich cultural and religious heritage."], 'Key Features': ['Architectural Design: The mosque features a central aquamarine dome surrounded by 52 smaller domes and a white minaret. name: King Fahad's Fountain
description: {'Information': ["King Fahd's Fountain, also known as the Jeddah Fountain, is the tallest of its kind globally. Constructed between 1980 and 1983 and inaugurated in 1985, it was a gift from King Fahd bin Abdulaziz to the city of Jeddah. Located along the Jeddah Corniche on the Red Sea coast, the fountain is visible from various points in the city.", "The fountain stands as a testament to Jeddah's modernization and development. Inspired by Geneva's Jet d'Eau, it showcases advanced engineering and design, becoming a symbol of the city's identity."], 'Key Features': ['Height: Jets water up to 312 meters (1,024 feet), surpassing structures like the Eiffel Tower.', 'Water Velocity: Emits water at speeds up to 375 km/h (233 mph), with a mass exceeding 16 tons airborne at any moment.', 'Design: Features a base shaped like a traditional Arabian incense burner, reflecting cultural heritage.', 'Lighting: Illuminated by over 500 high-intensity spotlights at night, enhancing its visual appeal.'], 'Working Hours': ["The fountain operates daily, with shows commencing at sunset and continuing until midnight. It's best to arrive early to secure optimal viewing spots along the Corniche.", 'Best Viewing Times: Evenings offer illuminated views, with shows typically starting at sunset.', 'Access: Easily accessible via the Jeddah Corniche, with nearby cafes and restaurants for a complete experience.']}
short_description: King Fahd's Fountain is the world's tallest fountain in Jeddah, offering stunning water displays at night.

description: {'Information': ["teamLab Borderless Jeddah is an immersive digital art museum located in Jeddah's Historic District, Al-Balad. description: {'Information': ["Zawiya 97 is a cultural hub located in Jeddah's historic Al-Balad district, dedicated to preserving and revitalizing traditional crafts while fostering contemporary artistic expression.", "Named for the 97-degree angle from Jeddah to Mecca, Zawiya 97 serves as a bridge between heritage and innovation, symbolizing the connection between the city's rich past and its evolving creative landscape."], 'Key Features': ['Artisans Incubator Program: Supports craftsmen and makers in establishing their studios and selling products through Zawiya’s concept store.', 'Workshops and Exhibitions: Hosts events focusing on traditional crafts like "Mangour," a significant element of Hijazi architecture.', 'Community Engagement: Organizes cultural programs, residencies, and curated visits to promote cross-cultural exchange and artistic collaboration.'], 'Visiting Tips': ["Operating hours may vary depending on events and programs, it's advisable to consult Zawiya 97's official website or contact them directly before planning your visit."]}
short_description: A cultural hub in Al-Balad, Jeddah, blending traditional crafts with contemporary art.

description: {'Information': ["Al-Shafi'i Mosque, located in Jeddah's historic Al-Balad district, is considered the oldest mosque in the city, showcasing early Islamic architectural styles.", 'Parts of the mosque date back approximately 1,400 years to the era of Caliph Umar ibn Al-Khattab, highlighting its significance in Islamic history.'], 'Key Features': ['Constructed using traditional materials such as coral stones, bricks, and wood.', 'Features a distinctive minaret influenced by Ayyubid architecture, estimated to be over 900 years old.', 'Designed with an open courtyard for natural ventilation, reflecting early Islamic architectural principles.'], 'Visiting Tips': ['Open daily, visitors are advised to visit outside of prayer times.', 'Ideal to visit during non-prayer times to fully appreciate the architectural details.']}
short_description: Jeddah's oldest mosque, exemplifying early Islamic architecture with a 900-year-old minaret.

name: Al Sharbatly House
description: {'Information': ["Al Sharbatly House is a historic 20th-century mansion located in Jeddah's Al-Balad district, exemplifying traditional Hijazi architecture.", 'Constructed in the early 1900s by Al-Sharif Abdulilah Mihanna Al-Abdaly, the house was later purchased by Sheikh Abdullah Sharbatly, a prominent fruit importer.', 'It served as the headquarters of the Egyptian mission in Saudi Arabia for 20 years, hosting notable figures such as Talat Harb Pasha, founder of Banque Misr.'], 'Key Features': ['Four-story structure with a whitewashed facade.', 'Intricate wooden lattice balconies (mashrabiyas) and rawasheen designs.', 'Now functions as a cultural center hosting art exhibitions, music events, and craft workshops.'], 'Visiting Tips': ['Evening visits are recommended to experience the vibrant atmosphere of Al-Balad.', 'Hours vary ,check with local tourism sources before visiting.']}
